          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Update_UpdateSBMRAccounts",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to manage account records in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SBMR.SBMRAccount",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table. It processes an XML input containing account information, updates existing records, inserts new records, and deletes records that are no longer present in the input. The procedure ensures that the account data in the database reflects the current state as described by the XML input."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
